# Conventional Commits

When creating commits in this repository, use [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/en/v1.0.0/).

## Format

```
<type>(<optional scope>): <short description in imperative mood>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

- **Type** (English, lowercase): `feat`, `fix`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `perf`, `test`, `build`, `ci`, `chore`, `revert`.
- **Scope** (optional): area, e.g. `bot`, `docker`, `makefile`, `deps`.
- **Description**: imperative, no period at the end; Russian or English is fine; keep the line under ~72 characters when practical.

## Examples

- `feat(bot): add /start reply handler`
- `fix(docker): correct env file path in compose`
- `chore(deps): bump Go to 1.26.1`
- `ci: run preprod on pull requests`

## Breaking changes

Add `BREAKING CHANGE:` in the footer or append `!` after type/scope, e.g. `feat(api)!: drop legacy webhook format`.
